Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Received and Filed. Defense Letter to the Court - Case Status Change

Attorney Nicole A. Muller in court, defendant Timothy Romell Massey not in court, in custody.  Jon R Josephsen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for Status Conference. Defendant not produced. Defense counsel informs court that they are now in a resolution posture. Case adjourned for a Plea/Sentencing hearing to Br 16.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 21, 2022 at 10:00 am.

OFF THE RECORD- Attorney Nicole A. Muller in court, defendant Timothy Romell Massey not in court, in custody.  Jon R Josephsen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for Scheduling Conference. All parties appeared via zoom. Defendant not produced. Defense counsel informs court that they have received discovery materials and an offer from the state, but requests additional time to review with client. Case adjourned to Br 16.  Status conference scheduled for August 3, 2022 at 02:00 pm.

Request for Substitution of Judge received and filed.  Court consented to substitution against Judge Stark.  Parties are advised the Clerk of Circuit Court reassigned case pursuant to current court rules to Judge Gayson, Br. 16.

Defendant Timothy Romell Massey, appear by video in court with attorney Nicole A. Muller, appear by video.  Defendant Timothy Romell Massey in custody.  Karine O'Byrne appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Court too Judical Notice to case 16CF4546 & 21CF2345. Sworn for the State: MPD Officer C. Bayack.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 16.  Scheduling conference scheduled for July 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Timothy Romell Massey in court with attorney Colleen A Taylor.  Defendant Timothy Romell Massey in custody.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Timothy Romell Massey appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Stark, Branch 17.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 9, 2022 at 10:00 am.
